cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM

This paper deals with medical image analysis using deep neural networks and natural language processing. The focus is on automatic marking of regions of interest on images based on textual reports or keywords. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves language processing, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the second likely category. The use of deep neural networks for training and feature extraction makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also involves information retrieval and medical imaging, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia) as possible categories.
